Quote: It is important to note that the farms discussed in Chapter I to VI are 'one-man-units,' this type of farm having been used as it is most generally appropriate to the requirements of the returned servicemen with limited capital.<i>Ibid</i>28 A one man unit of this type will carry six hundred to a thousand ewes according to the suitability of the country for the breeding of replacements.
